edu.biu.scapi.securityLevel
Interface HashSecLevel

All Superinterfaces:
SecurityLevel
All Known Subinterfaces:
CollisionResistant, SHA1, SHA224, SHA256, SHA384, SHA512, TargetCollisionResistant
All Known Implementing Classes:
BcSHA1, BcSHA224, BcSHA256, BcSHA384, BcSHA512, CryptoPpSHA1, CryptoPpSHA224, CryptoPpSHA256, CryptoPpSHA384, CryptoPpSHA512, OpenSSLSHA1, OpenSSLSHA224, OpenSSLSHA256, OpenSSLSHA384, OpenSSLSHA512
public interface HashSecLevel
extends SecurityLevel

This hierarchy specifies the security level of a cryptographic hash function. The levels in this hierarchy are TargetCollisionResistant and CollisionResistant.

Author:
Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Yael Ejgenberg)
